comments: Adebayo (MIA) jumps vertically and absorbs the body contact with Barrett (NYK) during his driving shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) body during the drive.
Quickley (NYK) legally contests Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) and Lowry (MIA) come together and marginal contact occurs as they jostle for potential rebounding position.
Barrett (NYK) legally contests Butler's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs as he briefly grasps and immediately releases Jaquez Jr.'s jersey.
Adebayo (MIA) briefly grasps Hartenstein's (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs as they quickly disengage in pursuit of the rebound.
Brunson (NYK) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Lowry's (MIA) arm before Lowry makes his intended pass at the end of the drive.
Hartenstein (NYK) jumps vertically and brings his arm into a vertical position to legally contest Adebayo's (MIA) dunk attempt and any contact as they come together is incidental.
Jaquez Jr. (MIA) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession should remain with the Knicks.
Hartenstein (NYK) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Adebayo (MIA), which affects his play at the basket.
Lowry (MIA) initiates contact with Brunson's (NYK) arm, which affects Brunson's ability to maintain his dribble.
Barrett (NYK) legally contests Butler's (MIA) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
